# Hero pipeline: dry-run default

## User rule (standing)

- **All suggested `python3 generate_hero_images.py` commands use dry-run** (script default — do not add `--dry-run` or `--no-dry-run`).
- **Never put `--no-dry-run` in a command** unless the user explicitly asks for upload / Supabase / production / "kein dry-run".
- User terminal logs that contain `--no-dry-run` are often **their own debug runs** — not permission to copy that flag into suggestions.

## When giving commands

- Omit both `--dry-run` and `--no-dry-run` (default is local save under `~/sunnomad_output/`).
- Do not bundle "production" flags (`--no-dry-run`, sometimes `--no-review`) just because the task sounds like a batch or top-10 run.
- Upload / DB / filename behavior for `--no-dry-run` only if the user asks — not proactively.

## EU / US flags (separate from dry-run)

- EU batch: `--safe --eu` only.
- US batch: `--safe --us`.
- **Never suggest `--continental`** in batch commands — continental premium is auto-selected by `pick_premium_layer` (or not). Only add `--continental` if the user explicitly asks to force it.
- Same for other premium flags (`--noir`, `--viper`, `--eclipse`, `--sidewinder`, etc.) — auto or user-request only, not in default batch suggestions.
- Activities are on by default; use `--no-activities` to skip (do not add `--activity`).

## Before every command block

Ask: *Did the user explicitly request upload this turn?* If no → no `--no-dry-run`.
